== Ruby Idioms

This is the public repo for the ruby-idioms.com site.

== Site Goals

 * To foster a Ruby community that will contribute to helping new Ruby programmers in reading and writing Ruby code.
 * To help exercise your mind by encouraging daily programming practices 
 
== Features

Not complete, but a roadmap or todo list of sorts, completely subject to change of course.
 * oauth support for google/yahoo/github/etc accounts
 * tags (acts_as_taggable?)
 * version control
 * timeline view?
 * invites for beta period
 * category
 * other language support?
 * report posts
 * rating
 * wall of fame/shame
 * more to come...
 
== Help Needed

Any help, suggestions, etc are greatly appreciated.  For the project or contact @arcterex

